      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARDIGAN SNIPER (1) is a promising colt who took full advantage of this same barrier when he led and kept going to beat all of these rivals for a 4.3m win in the heat of this series at Kilmore. That was his second success from just three starts. He'll be very hard to catch again. There was plenty of merit in the debut effort of CLAYTON (5) when he came from a similar draw and raced outside CARDIGAN SNIPER before boxing on for second. Draws much wider than that rival again so it won't be easy to turn the tables but he does look to have some upside. SEABREEZE LAD (4) chased along the sprint lane for third in the heat, continuing his good form from SA where he came from the back row for a Globe Derby win two back. Trifecta hope along with BUILDTHEMANASTATUE (2) who draws well and will be fitter second up.",
